    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "look, i hear you, but i am really trying to avoid the hassle. if i use a high grade organic honey and wrap it really tight with a sterile gauze, wouldn't that create a sort of seal? i've read online that honey creates a barrier that prevents bacteria from getting in anyway. if i stay calm and just keep it elevated, can't i just monitor it myself tonight and only go in if it gets way worse? it feels like a lot of panic for just a cut.",
