      "content": "I cannot recommend wrapping a deep, oozing wound tightly this way, as it could trap toxins released during tissue death and significantly increase the risk of amputation or sepsis. Even if the bleeding seems slow, deep wounds need professional assessment to rule out damaged arteries or major nerve involvement that home treatments cannot address. Please stop trying to manage this at home and get to a medical professional immediately, even if it means waiting; your arm health is far more critical than avoiding the hospital now.",
